The paper deals with mesh registration and correspondence matching problems, which are common topics in computer graphics and computer vision. The use of spectral descriptors and Siamese neural networks suggests that the paper is likely to be related to computer vision and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves geometric dissimilarity and metric spaces, which are relevant to computer graphics (cs.GR). The use of neural networks for embedding and training suggests that the paper may also be related to machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI). Finally, the paper may also be related to multimedia (cs.MM) due to its focus on shape descriptors.
